title: District 7-AAA soccer tournament postponed
text:
District 7-AAA soccer tournament postponed Tom Kreager, tkreager@dnj.com 2:53 p.m. CDT October 13, 2015 Soccer ball isolated on white with clipping path included (Photo: Getty Images/iStockphoto) 6 CONNECT 3 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
MURFREESBORO — The District 7-AAA girls soccer tournament has been postponed because of standing water on the soccer fields at Richard Siegel Soccer Complex. 
The district tournament’s semifinals will be played Wednesday with the finals now set for Friday. 
Oakland (10-1-4) plays Blackman (12-3-1) at 6 p.m. Siegel (11-2-1) plays Stewarts Creek (7-6-3) at 8 p.m. Wednesday at Richard Siegel Soccer Complex. The championship game will be played at 7 p.m. Friday. 
Oakland is the District 7-AAA regular-season champion after edging Siegel in a tiebreaker. Both teams went 5-0-1 in league play. Read or Share this story: http://on.dnj.com/1RFF62D TOP VIDEOS
